{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Rectangle\/geometryGroup()"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" may be added and removed at different times the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"applied.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"parent view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"remoteSource":{"fileName":"RendererEffect.swift","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L294"},"role":"symbol","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","platforms":[{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"iOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"10.15"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"13.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"visionOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"1.0"},{"unavailable":false,"beta":false,"name":"watchOS","deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"6.0"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwiftUICore9RectangleV","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/rectangle\/geometrygroup()"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Rectangle"]]},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Rectangle/geometryGroup()":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Rectangle\/geometryGroup()","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"View","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"geometryGroup()","abstract":[{"text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from its parent view.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/rectangle\/geometrygroup()"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Rectangle":{"abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular shape aligned inside the frame of the view containing it.","type":"text"}],"title":"Rectangle","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Rectangle","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/rectangle","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Rectangle","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rectangle","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"View","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","role":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]}}}